  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">BT Mic Loan I</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">I.	The most significant project-level outcome would be achieved through increased access to microfinance for underserved groups of the population, particularly women borrowers.

II.	IFC investment will result in significant changes in microfinance segment through innovation, demonstration effects, and capacity building.

III.	Supporting longer term lending to MSEs - by far the largest group in the private sector - will also positively contribute to strengthening entrepreneurship and employment growth in Romania, particularly in rural areas and among women.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed project involves a straight senior loan of up to US$16 million equivalent in RON, to be provided to BT Microfinantare IFN SA (the Company or BT Mic), a fully-owned subsidiary of Banca Transilvania S.A. (BT or the Bank). The proceeds of the loan will be used to support the Companys local currency financing of micro and small enterprises (MSEs) in Romania with at least 50% of the proceed used to support lending to women owned or managed micro and small enterprises.</narrative>
  </description>
